replyContent: You gave it one star because it does not work perfectly on a device that has the worst ever implementation of Android? I think it should be applauded even to start up... The video import just copies the video file to the "raw video" folder. If you want to import GoPro GPS data you need to select a different import type "GoPro sensor data".

content: Fantastic! quite powerful if you put the time into learning to use it.

replyContent: If you contacted RaceChrono support we could help you with the app. It is an expert tool with initial learning curve, and might feel unintuitive at first.

I use the app in my circuit race car with an external GPS and it works brilliantly, I do not have a Go Pro camera but have one of these generic ones, video overlay is a breeze after the race day, support for the use of the app is amazing.

after *many* years: still works perfect to couple of 10ths to circuit transponders on my old s3, s4 and s8. does *exactly* what it says on the tin. rare bugs are always fixed by great fast support. i used a gopro 3+black and only internal sensors and got picture-in-picture overlays to make a great video. top app that produces great data for amateur racing and track days (s3 will only do hardware up to 720p for PIP so i set the gopro at 720p60wide non-protune just in case) v6.2.1 = perfect :-)
Just perfect
replyContent: Thank you for your updated feedback! Improving the backups is one of the main priorities going forwards with the app. Unfortunately a separate PC version is currently not feasible, as I need focus on the mobile apps, to make sure they are as good as they can be. That said using this app on a 9" or 10" tablet will probably help you a lot!

replyContent: Where and how do you have the Pixel 2 installed? When using the internal GPS, it's critical to have the phone in a holder, with clear view to sky and satellites. It will not work from your pocket. For that you'll need an external GPS, and then you can keep the phone where you like.

content: This is a quality app when it works, but my last two visits to Brands Hatch won't record any sessions for laps. I'm not sure if it's an update issue, but currently at Brands now and still not working
replyContent: Please contact RaceChrono support, it may be a track setup or GPS signal problem. If it's track setup problem, it can be mended afterwards and you'll see your laps afterwards.

content: Very well made, worth the price. I use it every time I go on a track day.
Great app love it

Sometimes it forgets to record laps and ui is really cluncky edit: I appreciate your reply, I'd be hapoy to reconsider my review if the app improves. My main problem with ui is that I need to always select a track every time I get back on track. Why can't it just default to the last track of the day? How many people do drive more than a track a day? If gps is so bad that my times won't be recorded it would be nice to know so in advance, or at the very least after I finished my session. The idea of a session is nice, but these things are called track days... It would be nice to be able to group, compare and export data by event. Also grouping by track (using older sessions from same track) would be nice.
replyContent: Thank you for updating your review. You can already record your track day to one session by resuming it after a pause. This way no need to re-select track either. My app doesn't know if users are on a race, track day or commuting to work, so that's why call them sessions. GPS data - the user needs to ensure proper reception as app cannot tell.

content: Excellent lap timer with video overlays!

A external GPS and OBD II are a must for this to be worth using.

The free version warrants 5 stars.. this version gets 10 stars.  Unbelievably simple to record and export a video with speed and RPM.  Immediately connected to my bluetooth GPS and OBDII reader.  A fantastic self-analysis tool.
Excellent app being using it since it's Symbian days. Really need the performance measuring features to make the app perfect again

We have been using RaceChrono Pro in its different alpha and beta versions this season at VLN Race Series at Nurburgring and are very pleased with it.  A few observations: - proper external GPS is a must, otherwise the quality of GPS data is not accurate enough. Phone's internal GPS may work on tracks which are flat, but not at the Ring. - Telephone's internal video is amazingly good. We only used Samsung S3 and were very positively surprised on the quality of the vid.
Minus a star for not loading all my data, devices (bluetooth obd2, bluetooth GPS), settings, tracks, etc. from the free version.  It takes me forever to set all that stuff up.
This is critical to me.  Really need ODB air fuel (measured).  This should be standard pid across cars.  What's the chance? Very impressed so far, not a single crash.
replyContent: The .csv files are intended to be readable by video overlay software, which themselves have units conversion settings. The units are metric to allow simple and robust reading at the other software. In Excel you can create math columns such as =(A1-32)*5/9. Please contact RaceChrono forum or support for further assistance.
